# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .prettierignore
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files that Prettier should not format.
#
# Prettier is used in this project for Markdown table alignment
# (via pre-commit manual stage and VS Code). However, it
# aggressively re-indents content inside Markdown files, which
# breaks mkdocstrings ::: directives that require specific
# indentation (e.g., docs/reference/api.md).
#
# This file tells Prettier to skip files where reformatting
# causes breakage.
#
# TODO (template users): Review and update this list after
#   customizing the project. Remove entries for files you don't
#   have and add entries for any files with sensitive formatting.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# mkdocstrings API reference — uses ::: directives with indented
# `options:` blocks that Prettier would flatten, breaking the
# MkDocs build.
docs/reference/api.md

# Generated / vendored
CHANGELOG.md
site/
node_modules/

# Build artifacts
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/

# Config files (TOML/YAML that Prettier may rewrite unhelpfully)
_typos.toml
repo_doctor.d/
.repo-doctor.toml
.github/

# Non-Markdown files that Prettier may try to touch
LICENSE
*.sqlite3
*.db

# Local data / scratch directories
var/
experiments/
